        YOU_RECEIVE_NOTHING_FROM_THE_MOON_RABBIT                                  = 7396,  -- You receive nothing from the moon rabbit...
        THE_MOON_RABBIT_HAS_BROUGHT_ALONG_A_MONSTER                               = 7397,  -- The moon rabbit has brought along a monster!
        YOU_HAVE_TO_DO_SOMETHING_ABOUT_THOSE_CRAZY                                = 7398,  -- You have to do something about those crazy trees, kupo!
        YOU_RE_DONE_FIGHTING_TREES_KUPO                                           = 7399,  -- You're done fighting trees, kupo?
        HEY_YOU_I_LL_HAVE_YOU_KNOW_THAT                                           = 7407,  -- Hey, you! I'll have you know that only the rightful leader of the Star Onion Brigade can sit there! Get down right now before I charge you with trees-on and disturbing the peas!
        I_DON_T_KNOW_HOW_YOU_GOT_INSIDE                                           = 7408,  -- I don't know how you got inside, but that area is off limits. Vacate the premises immediately!
        HE_HE_HERE_S_YOUR_DELIVERY_WHEEZE                                         = 7409,  -- He...he...here's your delivery...<wheeze>...!
        THANKS_ONCE_AGAIN_LIGHT_ON_YOUR_FEET_TODAY                                = 7410,  -- Thanks once again. Light on your feet today, I see!
        WALKING_TREES_HOW_POSITIVELY_PECULIAR_ARE_THESE_ALSO                      = 7411,  -- Walking trees!? How positively...peculiar. Are these also creations conjured up with Tarutaru magic?
        IN_THE_GUSTABERG_MOUNTAINS_OF_SOUTHERN_QUON_LIES                          = 7412,  -- In the Gustaberg Mountains of Southern Quon lies the industrial nation known as the Republic of Bastok.
        COMPARED_TO_SAN_D_ORIA_WITH_ITS_LEGENDARY                                 = 7413,  -- Compared to San d'Oria, with its legendary orders of knights, or Windurst, with its ancient institutes of magic, Bastok is still but a newborn nation.
        BUT_ADVANCED_TECHNOLOGY_AND_NEAR_LIMITLESS_UNDERGROUND_RESOURCES          = 7414,  -- But advanced technology and near limitless underground resources have allowed Bastok to rival the other two nations in power.
        INNOVATIVE_AND_ADAPTABLE_HUMES_MAKE_UP_MORE_THAN                          = 7415,  -- Innovative and adaptable Humes make up more than half the population of Bastok.
        WITH_THEIR_FLAIR_FOR_INDUSTRY_ECONOMY_AND_POLITICS                        = 7416,  -- With their flair for industry, economy, and politics, they were the driving force behind Bastok's rapid growth. Even now, Humes hold key positions in those areas.
        THE_GALKA_A_RACE_OF_HULKING_HUMANOIDS_COMPRISE                            = 7417,  -- The Galka, a race of hulking humanoids, comprise a third of Bastok's population. Originally hailing from Zepwell, they came to this land over six hundred years ago.
        WITHOUT_THEIR_INCOMPARABLE_STRENGTH_THE_COUNTLESS_ORE_MINES               = 7418,  -- Without their incomparable strength, the countless ore mines that drive Bastok's economy would never have been dug.
        ADVENTURERS_SEEKING_FAME_AND_FORTUNE_FLOCK_TO_RISING                      = 7419,  -- Adventurers seeking fame and fortune flock to rising nations like Bastok. You are one of them.
        YOUR_STORY_BEGINS_HERE_AMID_THE_SMOKE_AND                                 = 7420,  -- Your story begins here, amid the smoke and bustle of the industrial city of Bastok.
        HEY_GWILL_IS_IT_TRUE_YOU_REALLY_SAW                                       = 7421,  -- Hey, Gwill! Is it true? You really saw Captain Volker!?
        ARE_YOU_REALLY_REALLY_SURE_WE_RE_TALKING                                  = 7422,  -- Are you really, really sure? We're talking about the captain of the Mythril Musketeers here!
        I_M_TELLING_YOU_I_M_SURE_I                                                = 7423,  -- I'm telling you, I'm sure! I saw him walking toward the Mines District. I bet you he's investigating something!
        YEAH_RIGHT_LIKE_YOU_D_EVER_KNOW                                           = 7424,  -- Yeah, right! Like you'd ever know!
        ID_7425                                                                   = 7425,  -- ...
        HEY_DIDN_T_YOU_SAY_YOU_WANTED_TO                                          = 7426,  -- Hey, didn't you say you wanted to become a Mythril Musketeer someday?
        YOU_RE_TOO_SLOW_THEY_D_NEVER_TAKE                                         = 7427,  -- You're too slow. They'd never take you! Besides, Galka can't become Musketeers! Even if they did, they'd never become captains!
        THAT_S_NOT_TRUE_TWO_OF_THE_FIVE                                           = 7428,  -- That's not true! Two of the five Mythril Musketeers are Galka...
        BUT_ONE_OF_EM_DISAPPEARED_A_LONG_TIME                                     = 7429,  -- But one of 'em disappeared a long time ago, right? He doesn't count!
        AND_AND_THERE_WAS_EVEN_A_GALKA_WHO                                        = 7430,  -- And...and...there was even a Galka who was supposed to become a captain, once...
        HA_THAT_S_A_LAUGH_WHOEVER_TOLD_YOU                                        = 7431,  -- Ha! That's a laugh! Whoever told you that?
        GUMBAH_FROM_THE_MINES_DISTRICT                                            = 7432,  -- Gumbah, from the Mines District...
        HE_S_JUST_A_KID_WHAT_WOULD_HE                                             = 7433,  -- He's just a kid! What would he know?
        AND_I_CAN_T_BELIEVE_YOU_D_HANG                                            = 7434,  -- And I can't believe you'd hang around that dirty ol' place! Well, we're not playing with grubby Mines people like you!
        HEY_HEY_WHAT_S_ALL_THIS_BICKERING_ABOUT                                   = 7435,  -- Hey, hey. What's all this bickering about?
        DAD_ARE_YOU_GOING_ADVENTURING_AGAIN                                       = 7436,  -- Dad! Are you going adventuring again?
        I_AM_I_LL_BE_GONE_AWHILE_BUT                                              = 7437,  -- I am. I'll be gone awhile, but if you don't get along with the other kids, I won't bring you any presents...
        YES_SIR                                                                   = 7438,  -- Yes, sir!
        YOU_RE_GOING_TOO_MISTER_DALZAKK                                           = 7439,  -- You're going too, Mister Dalzakk?
        YES_BE_GOOD_AND_LOOK_AFTER_MY_PLACE                                       = 7440,  -- Yes. Be good and look after my place for me, Gwill.
        HEY_LET_S_GO_PLAY_OVER_THERE                                              = 7441,  -- Hey, let's go play over there!
        H_HEY_GUYS_WAIT_FOR_ME                                                    = 7442,  -- H-hey, guys! Wait for me!
        WELL_THEN_LET_S_OH                                                        = 7443,  -- Well then, let's... Oh?
        YOU_RE_AN_ADVENTURER_TOO_I_SEE_AH                                         = 7444,  -- You're an adventurer too, I see. Ah, but you're still new, aren't you? I can't ask you to come with us, then.
        LIKE_DALZAKK_AND_MYSELF_HAVE_DONE_YOU_SHOULD                              = 7445,  -- Like Dalzakk and myself have done, you should try to find a party of people who are the same level as you.
        WE_DO_NOT_ALWAYS_ADVENTURE_TOGETHER                                       = 7446,  -- ...We do not always adventure together...
        RIGHT_IS_THERE_ANYTHING_WE_CAN_HELP_YOU                                   = 7447,  -- ...Right. Is there anything we can help you with? What is it you want to do first?
        FOR_STARTERS_I_D_LIKE_TO_FIGHT_MONSTERS                                   = 7448,  -- For starters, I'd like to... Fight monsters! Go shopping. Find some work.
        THEN_YOU_WANT_TO_BE_OUTSIDE_THE_CITY                                      = 7449,  -- Then you want to be outside the city walls. Head southwest of here and you'll find the West Gate.
        ALWAYS_CHECK_YOUR_TARGET_S_STRENGTH_BEFORE_ENGAGING                       = 7450,  -- Always check your target's strength before engaging it and make sure it won't eat you whole.
        YOU_RE_STANDING_IN_THE_BASTOK_MARKETS_YOU                                 = 7451,  -- You're standing in the Bastok Markets. You should find everything you need in this district.
        ON_THE_KULATZ_BRIDGE_NEAR_THE_WEST_GATE                                   = 7452,  -- On the Kulatz Bridge near the West Gate you'll find the Dragon's Claws weaponry store, Brunhilde's armor shop, and Mjoll's goods shop. Sororo's magic shop and the entrance to the Metalworks are in the northern section.
        SETTING_GOALS_FOR_YOURSELF_THAT_S_GOOD_WHAT                               = 7453,  -- Setting goals for yourself, that's good. What kind of work are you looking for?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_TO_DO_SERVE_BASTOK                                       = 7454,  -- What do you want to do? Serve Bastok. Help people. Get rich, quick.
        AH_A_PATRIOT_YOU_WANT_TO_TALK_TO                                          = 7455,  -- Ah, a patriot! You want to talk to a guard in charge of assigning missions. You should be able to find one at the West Gate. That's southwest of here.
        HMM_I_DON_T_THINK_I_KNOW_ANYONE                                           = 7456,  -- Hmm... I don't think I know anyone in need of help right now.
        I_DO_HER_NAME_IS_MICHEA_SHE_S                                             = 7457,  -- I do. Her name is Michea. She's an Elvaan who lives next door to me. Could you talk to her and see if you can help?
        GO_TO_THE_KULATZ_BRIDGE_NEAR_THE_WEST                                     = 7458,  -- Go to the Kulatz Bridge near the West Gate. There you will see three buildings with shops in them. Michea lives on the second floor of the middle building.
        WHY_DON_T_YOU_HELP_HER_YOURSELF                                           = 7459,  -- Why don't you help her yourself?
        ID_7460                                                                   = 7460,  -- ...
        FINE_I_WON_T_ASK_WELL_THERE_YOU                                           = 7461,  -- Fine, I won't ask. Well, there you have it.
        THEN_YOU_SHOULD_GO_TO_GOLD_STREET_WHERE                                   = 7462,  -- Then you should go to Gold Street, where Bastok's rich and famous live. It runs along the canal east of here. You should have no trouble finding some high-paying work there.
        ANYWAY_HERE_TAKE_THIS_GIVE_IT_TO_A                                        = 7463,  -- Anyway...here, take this %. Give it to a guard named Reet, and she'll give you some starting money.
        YOU_CAN_FIND_HER                                                          = 7464,  -- You can find her...
        HERE_OPEN_THE_MAP_FROM_THE_MAIN_MENU                                      = 7465,  -- Here. Open the Map from the main menu on the right if you want to check it again.
        USE_TRADE_FROM_THE_MAIN_MENU_TO_GIVE                                      = 7466,  -- Use Trade from the main menu to give items to people. Reet will tell you more about that.
        WELL_WE_REALLY_SHOULD_BE_GOING_GOOD_LUCK                                  = 7467,  -- Well, we really should be going. Good luck on your travels, adventurer.
        I_SAY_ARE_YOU_AN_ADVENTURER_LOOKING_FOR                                   = 7468,  -- I say, are you an adventurer? Looking for some work?
        ARE_YOU_LOOKING_FOR_WORK_YES_NO                                           = 7469,  -- Are you looking for work? Yes. No.
        THEN_I_HAVE_NO_BUSINESS_WITH_YOU_OUT                                      = 7470,  -- Then I have no business with you. Out, I say! Out!
        LET_ME_INTRODUCE_MYSELF_I_AM_HORATIUS_THE                                 = 7471,  -- Let me introduce myself. I am Horatius, the foremost gem collector in all of Bastok.
        I_VE_COLLECTED_EVERY_SINGLE_KIND_OF_PRECIOUS                              = 7472,  -- I've collected every single kind of precious gem, but now I want to get my hands on a rare stone of a different kind.
        I_D_LIKE_TO_GET_MY_HANDS_ON                                               = 7473,  -- I'd like to get my hands on something called %.
        AS_YOU_CAN_GUESS_FROM_THE_NAME_THE                                        = 7474,  -- As you can guess from the name, the Dangruf Wadi is where you'd want to look. What's more, legend says that it can only be found on bright, sunny days.
        IF_YOU_MANAGE_TO_GET_YOUR_HANDS_ON                                        = 7475,  -- If you manage to get your hands on %, bring it to me. You will be greatly rewarded.
        AH_GOOD_WORK_GOOD_WORK_HERE_IS_YOUR                                       = 7476,  -- Ah! %! Good work, good work! Here is your reward!
        WHAT_A_STRANGE_WONDROUS_STONE_I_THINK_I                                   = 7477,  -- What a strange, wondrous stone... I think I want more of these!
        MY_HUSBAND_SAYS_HE_S_A_COLLECTOR_BUT                                      = 7478,  -- My husband says he's a collector, but I must say he doesn't have much taste.
        HE_SIMPLY_DOESN_T_KNOW_WHAT_TO_DO                                         = 7479,  -- He simply doesn't know what to do with all that money he made during the Crystal War forging cannons for the Republic.
        WELL_WELL_WHAT_DO_WE_HAVE_HERE_AN                                         = 7480,  -- Well, well. What do we have here? An adventurer, I'd say. Yes, you do have that eager look on your face.
        WELL_SINCE_YOU_RE_HERE_YOU_MIGHT_AS                                       = 7481,  -- Well, since you're here, you might as well do some work for me. A monster took my parcel from the courier who was carrying it.
        THE_COURIER_SAID_THAT_HE_WAS_ATTACKED_NEAR                                = 7482,  -- The courier said that he was attacked near the lighthouse in South Gustaberg. The adventurer I sent before failed to catch it, and the beast won't come out anymore.
        THERE_MUST_BE_A_WAY_TO_LURE_IT                                            = 7483,  -- There must be a way to lure it out. I would have asked Dalzakk--he is very informed in such matters--but he's out of town, adventuring. <Sigh> What is it with you people and this adventuring business?
        IF_YOU_MANAGE_TO_BRING_IT_BACK_TO                                         = 7484,  -- If you manage to bring it back to me, though, I'll give you a reward. I know that's what you people want.
        IF_YOU_RE_LOOKING_FOR_MISTER_DALZAKK_HE                                   = 7485,  -- If you're looking for Mister Dalzakk, he's gone adventuring for a while.
        THE_MONSTER_IN_THE_LIGHTHOUSE_YEAH_ACTUALLY_I                             = 7486,  -- The monster in the lighthouse? Yeah, actually, I've heard Mister Dalzakk talk about it before. I think you have to put % behind the lighthouse to lure it out.
        HE_SAID_YOU_HAVE_TO_TRADE_WITH_SELECTABLE                                 = 7487,  -- He said you have to Trade with selectable points on the field to use or place items. Does that help?
        GOOD_YOU_GOT_IT_HERE_S_YOUR_REWARD                                        = 7488,  -- Good, you got it. Here's your reward.
        BASTOK_IS_A_WELLSPRING_OF_RARE_AND_PRECIOUS                               = 7489,  -- Bastok is a wellspring of rare and precious gems...and I swear on my collector's pride, I will have them all!
        HMM_WHAT_DO_YOU_WANT_FROM_ME_GET                                          = 7490,  -- Hmm? What do you want from me? Get out! Out!
        IF_YOU_RE_LOOKING_FOR_MISTER_DALZAKK_HE_2                                 = 7491,  -- If you're looking for Mister Dalzakk, he's out adventuring. He lets me stay here and read his books while he's away.
        HM_WHAT_S_THIS_I_M_READING_NOW                                            = 7492,  -- Hm? What's this I'm reading now? It's called The Chronicles of Prien the Brave. It's the biography of some famous president that ruled during the Crystal War.
        I_FIRST_PICKED_THE_BOOK_UP_BECAUSE_OF                                     = 7493,  -- I first picked the book up because of the interesting engravings on its binding, but after reading a few pages, I felt a deeper connection to the story.
        I_WONDER_IF_IT_HAS_SOMETHING_TO_DO                                        = 7494,  -- I wonder if it has something to do with the bronze bullet I found myself clenching upon my rebirth...
        WELL_MET_ADVENTURER_MY_NAME_IS_NUDARA_I                                   = 7495,  -- Well met, adventurer. My name is Nudara. I was once master of this fine guild. I now occasionally drop in to give advice to the young adepts, though they rarely have the time to lend their ears to the musings of a grizzled, old goldsmith.
        AS_YOU_CAN_SEE_THESE_DAYS_EXOTIC_METALS                                   = 7496,  -- As you can see, these days, exotic metals such as platinum and orichalcum line the guild's shelves like weeds in a garden.
        HOWEVER_WHEN_I_WAS_STILL_YOUNG_THE_DISTRIBUTION                           = 7497,  -- However, when I was still young, the distribution of most all metals, from bronze to silver, was regulated by the Republic. It was a struggle to find enough resources to forge a simple ring.
        IT_WAS_REGULATIONS_SUCH_AS_THOSE_THAT_IMPELLED                            = 7498,  -- It was regulations such as those that impelled us to focus on our techniques. It gave young soldiers a reason to spend a whole month's wages on something special to leave their loved ones before marching off to the front.
        I_SHALL_ALWAYS_TREASURE_THE_THOUGHT_THAT_MY                               = 7499,  -- I shall always treasure the thought that my skill brought a glimmer of happiness in an age so filled with sorrow.
        YAWN_GUESS_I_LL_SKIP_WORK_TODAY_TOO                                       = 7500,  -- <Yawn> Guess I'll skip work today, too...
        OOPS_YOU_HEARD_THAT_I_WORK_IN_THE                                         = 7501,  -- Oops...you heard that? I work in the Metalworks, you see, but my work there is pretty boring. Doing the same thing over and over, every day of the week... It really gets to you after a while, you know?
        TAKE_FIREWATER_CIRCLE_FOR_INSTANCE_I_HEARD_THAT                           = 7502,  -- Take Firewater Circle, for instance. I heard that during the Crystal War, there used to be a giant tower right where the fountain is. Now wouldn't that be a sight to see?
        SIGH_WHY_CAN_T_THERE_BE_A_NEW                                             = 7503,  -- <Sigh>... Why can't there be a new war, or something? Then, I could quit this dead-end job and enlist in the Republican Legion!
        WITH_MY_BRAINS_I_D_BE_A_COMMANDER                                         = 7504,  -- With my brains, I'd be a commander in no time! Just don't ask me to go to the front lines... I have this thing about dying...
        HUNGRY_WOLF_TOLD_YOU_ABOUT_YEAH_HE_S                                      = 7505,  -- Hungry Wolf told you about %? Yeah, he's a real gourmand, that one. Much like myself.
        IT_S_REALLY_HARD_TO_MAKE_AND_TAKES                                        = 7506,  -- It's really hard to make, and takes years of practice to perfect it and all that, but if you get this one special ingredient, even you can make one. Wanna know what that special ingredient is?
        IT_S_GOBLINS_NO_NOT_THE_GOBLINS_THEMSELVES                                = 7507,  -- It's Goblins. No, not the Goblins themselves, silly. They make this campfire up in the mountains that's got these special properties, see? All you have to do is stick % in it for just a little while...
        AND_PRESTO_YOU_GET_IT_S_AS_SIMPLE                                         = 7508,  -- And presto! You get %! It's as simple as that. Getting up there's not easy, but that shouldn't be a problem for an adventurer like you.
        AN_ADVENTURING_FRIEND_OF_MINE_BROUGHT_ONE_BACK                            = 7509,  -- An adventuring friend of mine brought one back to me once, and mmm-mmm! Boy, was it delicious!!!
        YOU_CAN_PUT_ITEMS_UP_FOR_SALE_OR                                          = 7510,  -- You can put items up for sale or bid for items at this auction house.
        PERSONALLY_I_BELIEVE_THAT_THE_JOY_OF_BIDDING                              = 7511,  -- Personally, I believe that the joy of bidding and buying items at these auctions is a privilege only true connoisseurs, such as myself, can fully appreciate.
        HERE_IN_THE_MARKETS_THEY_SELL_INSTRUMENTS_JEWELRY                         = 7512,  -- Here in the Markets, they sell instruments, jewelry, weapons, armor, goods... Anything anyone could ever want!
        THE_FUTURE_OF_THIS_CITY_IS_AS_BRIGHT                                      = 7513,  -- The future of this city is as bright as mine!
        MY_DAD_SAYS_THAT_IN_THIS_CITY_YOU                                         = 7514,  -- My dad says that in this city, you can do anything as long as you have the money to pay for it!
        EMRYS_IS_BRAGGING_HOW_HE_S_ALREADY_FINISHED                               = 7515,  -- Emrys is bragging how he's already finished collecting all his stamps! I haven't even started the stamp hunt yet!
        I_WASN_T_BRAGGING                                                         = 7516,  -- I wasn't bragging!
        SAY_CAN_YOU_GO_DO_IT_IN_MY                                                = 7517,  -- Say, can you go do it in my place? I can give you a reward. My family's rich, you know? Here, take my %.
        YOU_RE_HERE_FOR_THE_STAMP_HUNT_WHY                                        = 7518,  -- You're here for the stamp hunt? Why are adventurers doing it, I wonder. Never mind, here's your stamp.
        YOU_RECEIVED_A_STAMP                                                      = 7519,  -- You received a stamp!
        THANKS_HERE_YOU_GO                                                        = 7520,  -- Thanks! Here you go!
        ARAWN_AND_I_ARE_NEIGHBORS_YOU_KNOW                                        = 7521,  -- Arawn and I are neighbors, you know.
        THE_HOUSE_AT_THE_FAR_END_OF_THIS                                          = 7522,  -- The house at the far end of this canal is Arawn's house. Mine is next door to the west, across from Harmodios's Music Shop.
        THIS_BRIDGE_CONNECTS_THE_MINES_AND_THE_MARKETS                            = 7523,  -- This bridge connects the Mines and the Markets Districts.
        THE_GALKA_IN_THE_MINES_DISTRICT_ARE_A                                     = 7524,  -- The Galka in the Mines District are a rough lot. To tell you the truth, I'm glad I'm not on post there.
        MY_HUSBAND_S_ALWAYS_OFF_ADVENTURING_MY_SON                                = 7525,  -- My husband's always off adventuring, my son is out playing all day, and my stepfather keeps rambling about the strangest things...
        AUGH_I_MISS_BEING_SINGLE                                                  = 7526,  -- Augh! I miss being single...
        OH_NO_WE_RE_OUT_OF_AGAIN_I                                                = 7527,  -- Oh, no! We're out of % again. I wonder why...
        I_CAN_T_COOK_WITHOUT_FIRE_BUT_I                                           = 7528,  -- I can't cook without fire, but I don't have time to go shopping! Say, can you spare any %? If you have four of them, I'll buy them off you.
        GREAT_THANK_YOU_HERE_S_YOUR_MONEY_NOW                                     = 7529,  -- Great! Thank you! Here's your money. Now, stand back! It's cooking time!
        I_M_SORRY_I_DON_T_NEED_ANY                                                = 7530,  -- I'm sorry, I don't need any more % for now.
        HMM_AH_THE_HOT_SPRINGS_IN_THE_DANGRUF                                     = 7531,  -- Hmm? Ah, the hot springs in the Dangruf Wadi? Those were great! I felt like a new man after bathing there!
        I_WISH_THEY_HAD_BEEN_BUILT_BACK_WHEN                                      = 7532,  -- I wish they had been built back when I was a legion praefectus...
        YOU_WANNA_MAKE_MONEY_BUY_CHEAP_AND_SELL                                   = 7533,  -- You wanna make money? Buy cheap, and sell high! That's my motto!
        THE_MERCHANTS_IN_THE_CITY_ARE_ALL_CROOKS                                  = 7534,  -- The merchants in the city are all crooks! Don't buy from them--they'll rob you blind! Buy items cheap from people who don't need them.
        THEN_SELL_THEM_TO_PEOPLE_WHO_DO_FOR                                       = 7535,  -- Then sell them to people who do--for more than what you bought them for, of course! Check people out to see what kind of items they're likely to be looking for. That's how you do business!
        YOU_LOOK_SURPRISED_YOU_FIND_IT_UNUSUAL_TO                                 = 7536,  -- You look surprised. You find it unusual to see a lady of high birth standing in her own kitchen, perhaps?
        I_BELIEVE_THAT_COOKING_IS_A_REFINED_HOBBY                                 = 7537,  -- I believe that cooking is a refined hobby worthy of one such as me. I only use the best ingredients gil can buy, of course.
        WELL_NOW_WHAT_SHOULD_I_MAKE_TODAY_OH                                      = 7538,  -- Well now, what should I make today? Oh, I have not done the groceries yet...do you happen to have anything to spare?
        BREAKFAST_BREAKFAST_I_WONDER_WHAT_S_FOR_BREAKFAST                         = 7539,  -- Breakfast, breakfast, I wonder what's for breakfast?t Maybe, maybe, just maybe, a salad with %?t
        LUNCH_LUNCH_LUNCH_LUNCH_I_WONDER_WHAT_S                                   = 7540,  -- Lunch, lunch, lunch, lunch, I wonder what's for lunch?t Maybe, maybe, just maybe, a stew with %?t
        DINNER_DINNER_I_WONDER_WHAT_S_FOR_DINNER                                  = 7541,  -- Dinner, dinner, I wonder what's for dinner?t Maybe, maybe, just maybe, delicious, saut%ied %?t
