        WHAT_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_KNOW_ABOUT_BASIC                                   = 8424,  -- What would you like to know about? Basic rules. Official/private matches. Flammen-Brenner. Flamme. Match score. Petras and quarrying. Sprint. KO. Return.
        THE_BASIC_RULES_OF_BRENNER_ARE_AS_FOLLOWS                                 = 8425,  -- The basic rules of Brenner are as follows:
        FIRST_THE_PARTICIPANTS_DIVIDE_INTO_TWO_TEAMS_EACH                         = 8426,  -- First, the participants divide into two teams. Each side's camp contains the same number of Flammen-Brenner.
        AT_THE_BEGINNING_OF_THE_MATCH_HALF_OF                                     = 8427,  -- At the beginning of the match, half of each side's Flammen-Brenner will be ablaze with Flamme, or flame, while the other half will remain unlit.
        PARTICIPANTS_CAN_SEIZE_A_FLAMME_FROM_THE_OPPOSING                         = 8428,  -- Participants can seize a Flamme from the opposing side's Flammen-Brenner and carry it around the Isle.
        THE_GOAL_IS_TO_STEAL_YOUR_OPPONENT_S                                      = 8429,  -- The goal is to steal your opponent's Flamme and use them to light your side's Flammen-Brenner.
        THE_SIDE_THAT_SUCCEEDS_IN_LIGHTING_ALL_OF                                 = 8430,  -- The side that succeeds in lighting all of its Flammen-Brenner will be declared the winner after a specified amount of time.
        IF_NEITHER_SIDE_IS_VICTORIOUS_BEFORE_THE_MATCH                            = 8431,  -- If neither side is victorious before the match ends, the outcome will be judged based on the score. The match score section of the rulebook contains more information on this subject.
        BRENNER_IS_SIGNIFICANTLY_DIVIDED_INTO_PUBLIC_AND_PRIVATE                  = 8432,  -- Brenner is significantly divided into public and private matches. Official matches are held periodically according to level and feature general participation.
        YOU_CANNOT_RESERVE_THE_ISLE_WHEN_AN_OFFICIAL                              = 8433,  -- You cannot reserve the Isle when an official match is being held.
        NO_ITEMS_ARE_NECESSARY_FOR_PARTICIPATION_BUT_A                            = 8434,  -- No items are necessary for participation, but a minor fee will be collected. You will be unable to participate if your level is too low.
        THE_MATCH_OUTCOME_WILL_BE_RECORDED_UNLESS_THE                             = 8435,  -- The match outcome will be recorded unless the number of participants fails to exceed # members, or if there are fewer than # members in a match where the two sides' numbers differ. In such cases, the game will be considered a training match and will not be recorded.
        PRIVATE_MATCHES_REQUIRE_A_RESERVATION_AND_PARTICIPATION_MAY               = 8436,  -- Private matches require a reservation, and participation may be limited. The Master of Ceremonies (MC) can freely adjust the rules and control match proceedings.
        LS_LIGA_IS_A_FORM_OF_PRIVATE_MATCH                                        = 8437,  -- LS Liga is a form of private match. You can learn more about LS Liga by speaking to a Marshal.
        A_FLAMMEN_BRENNER_IS_A_DEVICE_THAT_CONTAINS                               = 8438,  -- A Flammen-Brenner is a device that contains a Flamme (flame). The Flammen-Brenner is covered by a grate that will open after taking a set amount of damage, exposing the Flamme.
        THE_PARTICIPANTS_MUST_UTILIZE_THIS_CHANCE_TO_SEIZE                        = 8439,  -- The participants must utilize this chance to seize the Flamme before the grate recloses. Once the grate is closed, the Flammen-Brenner will begin recovering from the damage it has been dealt.
        IF_YOU_MANAGE_TO_OPEN_THE_OPPOSING_TEAM                                   = 8440,  -- If you manage to open the opposing team's Flammen-Brenner and capture their Flamme, you should make haste to light one of the Flammen-Brenner on your side.
        AFTER_A_CERTAIN_AMOUNT_OF_TIME_THE_FLAMME                                 = 8441,  -- After a certain amount of time, the Flamme will burn out and the opposing team's Flammen-Brenner will be relit.
