        TRICK_OR_TREAT_I_VE_SEEN_THE_MOST                                         = 9467,  -- Trick or treat? I've seen the most sensationally scary costumes around town, kupo!
        WHAT_A_WONDERFUL_WITCH_HAT_KUPO_SINCE_YOU                                 = 9468,  -- What a wonderful witch hat, kupo! Since you've shown me your costume, I'll bring out some of my special merchandise, kupo!
        ARE_YOU_BRINGING_JOY_TO_THE_CHILDREN_OF                                   = 9469,  -- Are you bringing joy to the children of Vana'diel? Don't keep all that happiness to yourself, now!
        WHAT_S_THE_BEST_WAY_TO_MAKE_A                                             = 9470,  -- What's the best way to make a child smile? Why, presents, of course! Children nowadays want all kinds of goodies. I'm a bit behind the times, so I'm afraid I can't offer any good advice as to what would be the best present.
        BUT_IF_YOU_WANT_TO_AVOID_SUSPICION_YOU                                    = 9471,  -- But if you want to avoid suspicion, you'll need a red hat like mine. All smilebringers have them!
        THEY_SHOULD_BE_FOR_SALE_SOMEWHERE_AROUND_HERE                             = 9472,  -- They should be for sale somewhere around here, so snap one up if you want it!
        ID_9473                                                                   = 9473,  -- [You haven't brought any happiness to the children!/You've done some good./You have done fairly well./You have given the children much joy!/You have brought smile upon smile to the children!/You have the children bursting with glee!/The children love you!] [What a disappointment./You just need to give a little extra effort!/Keep it up!/You make a good smilebringer./Excellent work!/Stupendous job!/Even I think you're great!]
        YOU_CAN_MAKE_GOOD_USE_OF_SOME_OF                                          = 9474,  -- You can make good use of some of that joy you've brought to transport yourself to another nation. The children in other parts of Vana'diel need smiles, too!
        TRANSPORT_TO_ANOTHER_NATION_NOT_NOW_GO_TO                                 = 9475,  -- Transport to another nation? Not now. Go to San d'Oria. Go to Bastok. Go to Windurst.
        HAPPY_TRAVELS                                                             = 9476,  -- Happy travels!
        SORRY_BUT_IT_LOOKS_LIKE_YOU_DON_T                                         = 9477,  -- Sorry, but it looks like you don't have enough joy and happiness in your life to do that. You can earn some by giving presents to children, though!
        LEAVE_THIS_HEAP_OF_FUTURE_FIREWOOD_TO_US                                  = 9478,  -- Leave this heap of future firewood to us, kupo! All we need from you is a couple cheers!
        WE_HAVE_TO_RUN_THIS_MONSTER_OUT_OF                                        = 9479,  -- We have to run this monster out of town, kupo! The moogles will do all the work. All you have to do is cheer us along!
        BAD_TREE_BAD_TREE_WE_WON_T_LET                                            = 9480,  -- Bad tree! Bad tree! We won't let him get any further, kupo! Just keep cheering us on!
        THANKS_EVERYBODY_KEEP_IT_UP_AND_THERE_S                                   = 9481,  -- Thanks, everybody! Keep it up and there's no way we can lose, kupo!
        ID_10000_15000_30000_THE_TREE_IS_GAINING_TOO                              = 9482,  -- 10000... 15000... 30000! The tree is gaining too much power! This doesn't look good, kupo!
        UNNNNNNGH_BAD_TREE_WE_WON_T_LET_YOU                                       = 9483,  -- Unnnnnngh... Bad tree! We won't let you get in the way of our plans this time, kupo!
        NNNGAHHH_KUPO_I_CAN_T_HOLD_HIM_BACK                                       = 9484,  -- Nnngahhh, kupo! I can't hold him back!
        THE_TWINKLING_TREANT_SHEDS_A_SOLITARY_TEAR_AS                             = 9485,  -- The Twinkling Treant sheds a solitary tear as it fades into nothingness...
        WELL_THAT_WAS_INTERESTING_WHO_WOULD_HAVE_THOUGHT                          = 9486,  -- Well, that was interesting. Who would have thought that one of our festival trees would just get up and start walking around? I'm just glad that it is all over.
        HOWEVER_THERE_IS_SOMETHING_THAT_STILL_BOTHERS_ME                          = 9487,  -- However, there is something that still bothers me... It is like a dark cloud hanging over our fair city...
        I_VE_BEEN_SO_BUSY_FIGHTING_TREANTS_AND                                    = 9488,  -- I've been so busy fighting treants and spreading love to the children, that it wasn't until recently that I heard the rumors of the other smilebringers...
        I_DON_T_KNOW_WHAT_THESE_IMPOSTERS_ARE                                     = 9489,  -- I don't know what these imposters are cooking up, but if they are even thinking of laying a finger on the city's innocent children...
        I_HATE_TO_ASK_THIS_OF_A_STRANGER                                          = 9490,  -- I hate to ask this of a stranger, but you look like someone I can trust. Would you please be so kind as to search out the false smilebringer and bring him to me so we can straighten this whole mess out?
        YOU_RE_BACK_WERE_YOU_ABLE_TO_FIND                                         = 9491,  -- You're back! Were you able to find the imposter?
        YOU_LOCATED_HIM_BUT_HE_MANAGED_TO_ESCAPE                                  = 9492,  -- You located him, but he managed to escape? Well, I guess that is better than nothing. Now that he knows we are on to him, perhaps he will cease to prey on the Kingdom's children.
        I_HEARD_FROM_ANOTHER_KIND_ADVENTURER_THAT_THE                             = 9493,  -- I heard from another kind adventurer that the false smilebringer was passing out strange-looking boxes to the young ones... Why, for all I know, there could be live scorpions hiding in those packages, just waiting to sting the cute little button noses of all my little friends.
        YOU_DON_T_KNOW_HOW_MUCH_YOUR_KINDNESS                                     = 9494,  -- You don't know how much your kindness means to me. You're a little old to be my friend, but I'd like you to have this as a token of my appreciation.
        WOW_THAT_WAS_PRETTY_FRIGHTENING_I_M_ALL                                   = 9495,  -- Wow! That was pretty frightening. I'm all for tree's rights and everything, but once those guys start walking around my town...
        CHOP_EM_UP_AND_TOSS_THEM_ON_THE                                           = 9496,  -- Chop 'em up and toss them on the campfire, that's what I say. The only good tree is the one toasting my marshmallow.
        OH_YEAH_I_WANTED_TO_ASK_YOU_SOMETHING                                     = 9497,  -- Oh yeah, I wanted to ask you something before you interrupted me there.
        THERE_ARE_THESE_STRANGE_MIDGETS_RUNNING_AROUND_TOWN                       = 9498,  -- There are these strange midgets running around town claiming that they're smilebringers just like me.
        I_VE_HAD_MY_HANDS_SO_FULL_CHASING                                         = 9499,  -- I've had my hands so full chasing around the walking trees that I haven't been able to investigate. How about to make up for interrupting me back there, you go and see if you can find any juicy info on the fakes?
        I_LL_BE_RIGHT_HERE_PROTECTING_THE_FOUNTAIN                                = 9500,  -- I'll be right here protecting the fountain from any more treant attacks. Let me know the moment you've learned something worthwhile.
        WHO_THE_KEWPO_ARE_YOU_KEWPO_I_M                                           = 9501,  -- Who the kewpo are you, kewpo? I'm nothing doing wrong here, see? I'm smilebringing to nice boys and girls, kewpo! Move along! Move along!
        UMMM_I_CAN_EXPLAINING_KEWPO                                               = 9502,  -- Ummm... I can explaining, kewpo...
        JUST_NOT_TODAY_KEW_POOOOOOOOO                                             = 9503,  -- Just not today! Kew-pooooooooo!
        BACK_AT_LAST_DID_YOU_LEARN_ANYTHING_WORTH                                 = 9504,  -- Back at last. Did you learn anything worth my partially divided attention?
        UH_HUH_SO_YOU_LET_THE_THING_GET                                           = 9505,  -- Uh-huh... So you let the thing get away... Well, I guess that's what I get for relying on an amateur. My bad, my bad.
        ONE_OF_MY_OTHER_CONTACTS_TOLD_ME_THAT                                     = 9506,  -- One of my other contacts told me that the little spud was passing out some strange kind of pastry to all the kids. So far I haven't heard of any diarrhea breakouts, but the day is still young.
        I_GUESS_YOUR_SCARING_HIM_OFF_WILL_PUT                                     = 9507,  -- I guess your scaring him off will put an end to this fiasco, but we can't be one hundred percent sure. Keep your eyes out for that pest and next time don't let him escape!
        WHAT_YOU_WANT_SOMETHING_FOR_HELPING_ME_OUT                                = 9508,  -- What? You want something for helping me out? Well, it is the Starlight Celebration. Why not? You only get what you give, right?
