        THAT_S_THE_SPIRIT_YOU_RE_AN_ADVENTURER                                    = 14304,  -- That's the spirit! You're an adventurer in my spitting image...at least when it comes to passion.
        TODAY_S_LESSON_IS_ALL_ABOUT_RECORDS_OF                                    = 14305,  -- Today's lesson is all about Records of Eminence, so break out your textbook and turn to page five!
        WHAT_S_THAT_TSK_TSK_TSK_IF_YOU                                            = 14306,  -- What's that? Tsk, tsk, tsk. If you've forgotten your textbook, you'll have to share with the person next to you.
        LET_S_GET_THIS_SHOW_ON_THE_ROAD                                           = 14307,  -- Let's get this show on the road. Records of Eminence is, in a word...
        FIGHTING_SPIRIT                                                           = 14308,  -- ...fighting spirit!
        SO_WHAT_IF_THAT_S_TWO_WORDS_THAT                                          = 14309,  -- So what if that's two words!? That illustrates my point all the more. Adventurers need to give it eighty-thousand percent at all times if they want to uphold justice!
        CLASS_DISMISSED_NOW_GO_OUT_THERE_AND_DO                                   = 14310,  -- Class dismissed! Now go out there and do me proud.
        ANYTHING_TO_SAY_YESSIR_THAT_S_IT                                          = 14311,  -- Anything to say? Yessir! That's it?
        YOU_CAN_T_FOOL_ME_BY_JUST_ASSENTING                                       = 14312,  -- You can't fool me by just assenting to everything I say. That's not how education works. You'll never walk the path to enlightenment behaving like that!
        THAT_CURIOSITY_OF_YOURS_WILL_REALLY_TAKE_YOU                              = 14313,  -- That curiosity of yours will really take you places, lad/lass]. It's positively indispensable for any child of the Goddess.
        TO_TELL_THE_TRUTH_THOUGH_YOU_RE_ALREADY                                   = 14314,  -- To tell the truth, though, you're already well on your way to prominence!
        YOU_EVEN_COMPLETED_YOUR_FIRST_OBJECTIVE_SIMPLY_BY                         = 14315,  -- You even completed your first objective simply by talking to me. Furthermore, my experience tells me you'll be rewarded with some unusual type of compensation.
        NOW_TAKE_THE_NEXT_STEP_ON_YOUR_JOURNEY                                    = 14316,  -- Now, take the next step on your journey and try setting an objective all by yourself!
        NO_NEED_TO_BREAK_OUT_IN_A_SWEAT                                           = 14317,  -- No need to break out in a sweat--your eminent teacher will guide you. Just choose an objective under the Objective List in the Records of Eminence section of the Quests menu.
        I_HEAR_YOU_CAN_EVEN_REPEAT_CERTAIN_ONES                                   = 14318,  -- I hear you can even repeat certain ones. I'll let you figure out which ones they are on your own, though. I wouldn't want you to just regurgitate the answers I give you, now, would I?
        LIKE_I_HINTED_AT_BEFORE_YOU_GAIN_SPARKS                                   = 14319,  -- Like I hinted at before, you gain sparks of eminence that quantify your achievements. Trade them to me and I'll give you back some tokens of gratitude.
        WHOA_NOW_I_TEACH_MORE_ADVANCED_SUBJECTS_THAN                              = 14320,  -- Whoa, now. I teach more advanced subjects than you're able to understand at the moment. Try talking to Gulldago to learn the basics first.
        BY_THE_WAY_THIS_LITTLE_BUGGER_HERE_WHICH                                  = 14321,  -- By the way, this little bugger here, which we call %, records all your eminent feats for you.
        HM_OH_YES_I_TOO_SOMETIMES_BECOME_UNSETTLED                                = 14322,  -- Hm? Oh. Yes, I too sometimes become unsettled by its constant and intense glaring.
        LUCKILY_ALL_YOU_NEED_TO_DO_IS_TO                                          = 14323,  -- Luckily, all you need to do is to clap your hands together like so and...
        IT_VANISHES_INTO_THIN_AIR_SEE_EVEN_THIS                                   = 14324,  -- ...it vanishes into thin air. See, even this soulless machination possesses a fighting spirit. How else could it disappear instantaneously like that?
        JUST_KIDDING_I_M_ONLY_TRYING_TO_COVER                                     = 14325,  -- Just kidding. I'm only trying to cover up the fact that I don't know how it works. As my mentor always said, When you don't know the answer to a question, distract the person with a joke.
        WELL_I_VE_OFFICIALLY_TAUGHT_YOU_ALL_I                                     = 14326,  -- Well, I've officially taught you all I know. Go out into the world with your trusty % and prove how esteemed you truly are!
        I_ALWAYS_GET_A_LITTLE_TEARY_EYED_WHEN                                     = 14327,  -- ...I always get a little teary-eyed when I see my disciples go off to bigger and better things...<sniffle>
        PERHAPS_IT_WOULD_BEHOOVE_YOU_TO_SPEAK_WITH                                = 14328,  -- Perhaps it would behoove you to speak with Rolandienne in Southern San d'Oria (G-10).
        PERHAPS_IT_WOULD_BEHOOVE_YOU_TO_SPEAK_WITH_2                              = 14329,  -- Perhaps it would behoove you to speak with Isakoth in Bastok Markets (E-11).
        PERHAPS_IT_WOULD_BEHOOVE_YOU_TO_SPEAK_WITH_3                              = 14330,  -- Perhaps it would behoove you to speak with Fhelm Jobeizat in Windurst Woods (J-10).
        PERHAPS_IT_WOULD_BEHOOVE_YOU_TO_SPEAK_WITH_4                              = 14331,  -- Perhaps it would behoove you to speak with Eternal Flame in Western Adoulin (H-11).
        PERHAPS_IT_WOULD_BEHOOVE_YOU_TO_SPEAK_WITH_5                              = 14332,  -- Perhaps it would behoove you to speak with Nantoto in Lower Jeuno (H-8).
        INVISIBLE_EYES_UPON_YOU_CAUSE_THE_HAIRS_ON                                = 14333,  -- Invisible eyes upon you cause the hairs on the back of your neck to rise.
        THE_NODS_IN_AGREEMENT                                                     = 14334,  -- The % nods in agreement.
        A_NEW_RECORDS_OF_EMINENCE_OBJECTIVE_IS_NOW                                = 14335,  -- A new Records of Eminence objective is now available!
        A_NEW_RECORDS_OF_EMINENCE_OBJECTIVE_IS_NOW_2                              = 14336,  -- A new Records of Eminence objective, %, is now available!
        YOU_WISH_TO_EXCHANGE_YOUR_SPARKS                                          = 14337,  -- You wish to exchange your sparks?
        WAIT_BUT_A_MOMENT_HERE_FOLLOW_THIS_COMMAND                                = 14338,  -- Wait but a moment. Here, follow this command--er, compendium to the letter and you should be able to learn a thing or two.
        AH_THIS_ALMOST_SLIPPED_MY_MIND_SHOULD_YOU                                 = 14339,  -- Ah, this almost slipped my mind. Should you receive any distinct sorts of artifacts for completing an objective, I will be happy to take them off your hands.
        WORRY_NOT_FOR_I_AM_NOT_OUT_TO                                             = 14340,  -- Worry not, for I am not out to rob you of your glory. Quite the opposite, in fact. I will provide you with a worthwhile reward for collecting them.
        THANKS_TO_YOUR_DONATION_I_NOW_HAVE_IN                                     = 14341,  -- Thanks to your donation, I now have # in safekeeping.
        OHOHOHO_TURNING_IN_SPARKS_I_SEE                                           = 14342,  -- Ohohoho... Turning in sparks, I see.
        HOLD_YOUR_HOARDER_HARES_HERO_HEROINE_I_LOVE                               = 14343,  -- Hold your hoarder hares, hero/heroine]. I love your enthusiasm, but you're not going to learn a thing without a primer. Ahhh, here it is. Have a look-see.
        OH_CRUD_THAT_S_RIGHT_YOU_SHOULD_TRADE                                     = 14344,  -- Oh, crud, that's right. You should trade me any special artifacts you get from completing objectives.
        WHY_WHAT_A_GOOD_QUESTION_BECAUSE_I_LL                                     = 14345,  -- Why? What a good question! Because I'll give you a nifty-difty reward at some point, that's why.
        THANKS_FOR_DOING_WHAT_I_ASKED_NOW_I                                       = 14346,  -- Thanks for doing what I asked. Now I have a total of # from you.
        YOU_WANT_TO_TRRRADE_IN_SPARKS_DO_YOU                                      = 14347,  -- You want to trrrade in sparks, do you?
        LET_ME_WAKE_UP_FROM_MY_CATNAP_FIRST                                       = 14348,  -- Let me wake up from my catnap first... Alright, now rrread this.
        WAIT_WAIT_WAIT_IF_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_GET                                       = 14349,  -- Wait, wait, wait! If you happen to get any purrrticularly interesting items from completing objectives, send them my way.
        DON_T_WORRY_I_M_AS_HONEST_AS                                              = 14350,  -- Don't worry, I'm as honest as a cat when the meat's out of reach. I thought of taking them all for myself...
        BUT_I_DON_T_WANT_TO_MAKE_FUR                                              = 14351,  -- ...but I don't want to make fur fly with the Adventurers' Mutual Aid Network, so I'll do my job like a good little kitty.
        GRRREAT_NOW_I_HAVE_FROM_YOU_THANKS                                        = 14352,  -- Grrreat! Now I have # from you. Thanks!
        HM_OH_SPARK_EXCHANGE_OF_COURSE                                            = 14353,  -- Hm? Oh, spark exchange... Of course.
        I_M_NOT_COMPLETELY_SURE_BUT_THIS_MIGHT                                    = 14354,  -- I'm not completely sure, but this might help set some things straight...I guess.
        LET_ME_ADD_ONE_THING_PLEASE_FIND_IT                                       = 14355,  -- Let me add one thing. Please find it within your heart of hearts to give me anything of particular interest you get from completing objectives.
        I_LL_MAKE_IT_WORTH_YOUR_WHILE_I                                           = 14356,  -- I'll make it worth your while...I swear! Just keep at it and I'll be sure to surprise you with a hot, steaming helping of gratitude one day.
        THANKS_FOR_DOING_YOUR_PART_IN_THE_BATTLE                                  = 14357,  -- Thanks for doing your part in the battle for love and peace! With this latest addition, I'm now keeping track of # for you.
        RECORDS_OF_EMINENCE_IS_A_SYSTEM_BROUGHT_TO                                = 14358,  -- Records of Eminence is a system brought to you by the caring folks at the Adventurers' Mutual Aid Network. Set your own objectives whenever you desire, and fulfill them to receive compensation.
        TO_SET_THESE_TASKS_SELECT_OBJECTIVE_LIST_FROM                             = 14359,  -- To set these tasks, select 'Objective List' from the Quests menu, then choose ones that suit your fancy.
        YOU_WILL_BE_REWARDED_WITH_GIL_AND_SPARKS                                  = 14360,  -- You will be rewarded with gil and sparks of eminence, which serve the same function as points, notes, credits, and other such methods of quantifying one's greatness. As an extra incentive, adventurers will earn three times the amount of sparks for completing an objective the first time.
        COMPLETED_OBJECTIVES_WILL_VANISH_FROM_YOUR_QUEST_LIST                     = 14361,  -- Completed objectives will vanish from your quest list unless they are repeatable. In the event that you wish to make room for different objectives, you will need to remove them manually.
        AS_A_COROLLARY_REGARDING_REWARDS_YOU_LL_BE                                = 14362,  -- As a corollary regarding rewards, you'll be blessed with special remuneration once you complete several objectives. Bask in the joy of these pleasant surprises when you can.
        LASTLY_ANY_AND_ALL_ACTS_OF_VANDALISM_DIRECTED                             = 14363,  -- Lastly, any and all acts of vandalism directed against your % are strictly prohibited.
        SHOULD_YOU_BE_FOUND_IN_VIOLATION_OF_THIS                                  = 14364,  -- Should you be found in violation of this dictum, the heavens will part and wrath incarnate will descend to mete out justice upon you.
        THE_MAXIMUM_NUMBER_OF_THAT_MAY_BE_STORED                                  = 14365,  -- The maximum number of % that may be stored is #.
        YOU_DO_NOT_POSSESS_ENOUGH_TO_COMPLETE_THE                                 = 14366,  -- You do not possess enough % to complete the transaction.
        YOU_DO_NOT_POSSESS_ENOUGH_SPARKS_OF_EMINENCE                              = 14367,  -- You do not possess enough sparks of eminence to complete the transaction.
        YOU_HAVE_REACHED_THE_MAXIMUM_NUMBER_OF_SPARKS                             = 14368,  -- You have reached the maximum number of sparks that you can exchange this week (#). Your ability to purchase skill books and equipment will be restricted until next week.
        YOU_MAY_USE_UP_TO_MORE_SPARKS_OF                                          = 14369,  -- You may use up to # more sparks of eminence to purchase items.
        EXCHANGE_FOR_WHAT_SPARKS_ITEMS_SKILL_INCREASING_TOMES                     = 14370,  -- Exchange for what? (Sparks: #) Items. Skill-increasing tomes. Equ. Lv.1 - 9. (Up to #) Equ. Lv.10 - 19. (Up to #) Equ. Lv.20 - 29. (Up to #) Equ. Lv.30 - 39. (Up to #) Equ. Lv.40 - 50. (Up to #) Equ. Lv.51 - 70. (Up to #) Equ. Lv.71 - 98. (Up to #) Equ. Lv.99. (Up to #) 10. Trust. Exchange A.M.A.N. currencies. Exchange Seven Treasures. Wise words on Records of Eminence. Nothing.
        EXCHANGE_UP_TO_SPA_SPARKS_PREVIOUS_PAGE_NEXT                              = 14371,  -- Exchange up to # Spa. (Sparks: #) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) %. (#) Previous page. Next page. None.
        RECEIVE_HOW_MANY_SPARK_ONE_SPARK_THREE_SPARK                              = 14372,  -- Receive how many? (# spark[/s]) One. (# spark[/s]) Three. (# spark[/s]) Twelve. (# spark[/s]) Thirty-six. (# spark[/s]) None.
        ARE_YOU_SURE_YOU_WANT_TO_EXPEND_SPARK                                     = 14373,  -- Are you sure you want to expend # spark[/s] of eminence on this?
        MAKE_THE_EXCHANGE_YES_NO_2                                                = 14374,  -- Make the exchange? Yes. No.
        EXCHANGE_FOR_WHAT_ON_HAND_CURRENCIES_PROVISIONS_NONE                      = 14375,  -- Exchange for what? (On hand: #) Currencies. Provisions. None for the nonce.
        EXCHANGE_FOR_WHAT_ON_HAND_SPARKS_OF_EMINENCE                              = 14376,  -- Exchange for what? (On hand: #) Sparks of Eminence: #. Conquest Points: #. Imperial Standing: #. Allied Notes: #. Bayld: #. Valor Pts.: #. Aslt. Pts. (Leujaoam): #. Aslt. Pts. (T. Grounds): #. Aslt. Pts. (Lebros): #. Aslt. Pts. (Periqia): #. Aslt. Pts. (Ilrusi): #. Cruor: #. Kinetic Units: #. Obs. Fragments: #. M. Plasm Corpuscles: #. Ballista Points: #. (2000 max) Unity Accolades: #. Escha Silt: #. Resistance Credits: #. Nothing for the nonce.
        EXCHANGE_HOW_MANY_POINTS_ON_HAND_ONE_THREE                                = 14377,  -- Exchange how many points? (On hand: #) # (One). # (Three). # (Ten). # (Thirty). None.
        YOU_NOW_HAVE                                                              = 14378,  -- You now have # [sparks of eminence/conquest points/points of imperial standing/Allied Notes/bayld/Fields of Valor points/assault points (Leujaoam)/assault points (Mamool Ja Training Grounds)/assault points (Lebros Cavern)/assault points (Periqia)/assault points (Ilrusi Atoll)/cruor/kinetic units/obsidian fragments/mweya plasm corpuscles/ballista points/Unity accolades/pinches of Escha silt/resistance credits].
        BEWARE_THAT_ANY_AMOUNT_THAT_EXCEEDS_THE_MAXIMUM                           = 14379,  -- Beware that any amount that exceeds the maximum storage limit will unceremoniously vanish into the aether.
        EXCHANGE_FOR_WHAT_ON_HAND_NOTHING_FOR_THE                                 = 14380,  -- Exchange for what? (On hand: #) %. %. %. Nothing for the nonce.
        EXCHANGE_HOW_MANY_ON_HAND_ONE_THREE_TEN                                   = 14381,  -- Exchange how many? (On hand: #) One (#). Three (#). Ten (#). Thirty (#). None.
        TRULY_EXCHANGE                                                            = 14382,  -- Truly exchange # (#)?
        ARE_YOU_QUITE_SATISFIED_WITH_YOUR_SELECTION                               = 14383,  -- Are you quite satisfied with your selection?
        YOU_WISH_TO_EXCHANGE_AND_FOR_EQUIPMENT                                    = 14384,  -- You wish to exchange %, %, %, %, %, and % for equipment?
        EXCHANGE_FOR_WHAT_PREVIOUS_PAGE_NEXT_PAGE_NOTHING                         = 14385,  -- Exchange for what? %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. Previous page. Next page. Nothing for the nonce.
        THE_A_M_A_N_IS_PLEASED_TO                                                 = 14386,  -- The A.M.A.N. is pleased to announce a new service in which we purchase any equipment you no longer need--new or used.
        JUST_TRADE_ME_ANY_PIECE_OF_EQUIPMENT_YOU                                  = 14387,  -- Just trade me any piece of equipment you desire. I will quickly assess its value and award you with an appropriate number of reclamation marks.
        ONCE_YOU_ACCUMULATE_OF_THESE_MARKS_THEY_WILL                              = 14388,  -- Once you accumulate # of these marks, they will be automatically converted to one % and added to the total number held.
        THOUGH_I_AM_ONLY_AUTHORIZED_TO_ACCEPT_A                                   = 14389,  -- Though I am only authorized to accept a limited selection of equipment at present, the A.M.A.N. is considering making further additions to this list, so please check back regularly.
        WOULD_YOU_LIKE_RECLAMATION_MARK_IN_EXCHANGE_FOR                           = 14390,  -- Would you like # reclamation mark[/s] in exchange for one %? You currently have # mark[/s].
        PROCEED_WITH_THE_EXCHANGE_YES_NO                                          = 14391,  -- Proceed with the exchange? Yes. No.
        THE_RECLAIMER_AWARDS_YOU_WITH_RECLAMATION_MARK_FOR                        = 14392,  -- The reclaimer awards you with # reclamation mark[/s] for a total of #.
        THE_RECLAIMER_AWARDS_YOU_WITH_RECLAMATION_MARK_FOR_2                      = 14393,  -- The reclaimer awards you with # reclamation mark[/s] for a total of #. The number of % stored has increased by #.
        YOU_ARE_UNABLE_TO_TRADE_THAT_ITEM_AT                                      = 14394,  -- You are unable to trade that item at present.
        YOU_ARE_UNABLE_TO_TRADE_THAT_ITEM_BECAUSE                                 = 14395,  -- You are unable to trade that item because you cannot store any more %.
        ONLY_THOSE_PARTICIPATING_IN_RECORDS_OF_EMINENCE_MAY                       = 14396,  -- Only those participating in Records of Eminence may trade in items.
        YOU_CAN_T_SHAKE_THE_FEELING_THAT_YOU                                      = 14397,  -- You can't shake the feeling that you may be able to learn about Ygnas's whereabouts somewhere in this area.
        SPEAK_WITH_PLOH_TRISHBAHK_AT_CASTLE_ADOULIN_S                             = 14398,  -- Speak with Ploh Trishbahk at Castle Adoulin's front gates (K-9) and report what you have learned about Ygnas.
        WELCOME_TO_THE_DEEDS_OF_HEROISM_REWARDS_EXCHANGE                          = 14399,  -- Welcome to the Deeds of Heroism rewards exchange service!
        WHAT_WOULD_YOU_LIKE_TO_DO_CLAIM_A                                         = 14400,  -- What would you like to do? Claim a reward (~960 deeds). Claim a reward (970+ deeds). Use an A.M.A.N. voucher. Receive a %. What are Deeds of Heroism? Leave.
        DEEDS_OF_HEROISM_ARE_SPECIAL_POINTS_YOU_CAN                               = 14401,  -- Deeds of Heroism are special points you can earn by completing the Monthly Challenges available under the "Other" menu within the Records of Eminence.
        ONCE_YOU_HAVE_ACCUMULATED_A_CERTAIN_NUMBER_OF                             = 14402,  -- Once you have accumulated a certain number of Deeds, you can exchange them for various items.
        REWARDS_THAT_REQUIRE_970_DEEDS_OR_MORE_CAN                                = 14403,  -- Rewards that require 970 deeds or more can be reset by collecting a certain amount of deeds.
        THERE_ARE_MANY_FABULOUS_ITEMS_TO_BE_HAD                                   = 14404,  -- There are many fabulous items to be had, including some that will help you on your adventures, so try to earn as many Deeds as possible!
        DO_YOU_WANT_TO_USE_AN_A_M                                                 = 14405,  -- Do you want to use an A.M.A.N. voucher? %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. What are A.M.A.N. vouchers? Go back. Leave.
        IF_YOU_HAVE_AN_A_M_A_N                                                    = 14406,  -- If you have an A.M.A.N. voucher for an item such as a %, you can use it to choose from a list of corresponding items.
        DO_YOU_WANT_THE                                                           = 14407,  -- Do you want the %?
        DO_YOU_WANT                                                               = 14408,  -- Do you want # %?
        DO_YOU_WANT_THE_2                                                         = 14409,  -- Do you want the %?
        ARE_YOU_SURE_YOU_WANT_TO_PROCEED_YES                                      = 14410,  -- Are you sure you want to proceed? Yes. No.
        YOU_DO_NOT_POSSESS_ENOUGH_DEEDS_OF_HEROISM                                = 14411,  -- You do not possess enough Deeds of Heroism to receive this item.
        EXCHANGE_FOR_WHAT_PUMMELER_S_ARMOR_ANCHORITE_S                            = 14412,  -- Exchange for what? Pummeler's Armor. Anchorite's Attire. Theophany Attire. Spaekona's Attire. Atrophy Armor. Pillager's Attire. Reverence Armor. Ignominy Armor. Totemic Armor. Brioso Attire. Orion Attire. Wakido Armor. Hachiya Garb. Vishap Armor. Convoker's Attire. Assimilator's Attire. Laksamana's Attire. Foire Attire. Maxixi Attire. Maxixi Attire. Academic's Attire. Geomancy Attire. Runeist Attire. Go back. Leave.
        YOU_WILL_RECEIVE_THE_FOLLOWING_ITEMS_IN_THE                               = 14413,  -- You will receive the following items in the [/Pummeler's Armor/Anchorite's Attire/Theophany Attire/Spaekona's Attire/Atrophy Armor/Pillager's Attire/Reverence Armor/Ignominy Armor/Totemic Armor/Brioso Attire/Orion Attire/Wakido Armor/Hachiya Garb/Vishap Armor/Convoker's Attire/Assimilator's Attire/Laksamana's Attire/Foire Attire/Maxixi Attire/Maxixi Attire/Academic's Attire/Geomancy Attire/Runeist Attire] set.
        ID_14414                                                                  = 14414,  -- %.
        IS_THE_OKAY_YES_NO                                                        = 14415,  -- Is the [/Pummeler's Armor/Anchorite's Attire/Theophany Attire/Spaekona's Attire/Atrophy Armor/Pillager's Attire/Reverence Armor/Ignominy Armor/Totemic Armor/Brioso Attire/Orion Attire/Wakido Armor/Hachiya Garb/Vishap Armor/Convoker's Attire/Assimilator's Attire/Laksamana's Attire/Foire Attire/Maxixi Attire/Maxixi Attire/Academic's Attire/Geomancy Attire/Runeist Attire] okay? Yes. No.
        EXCHANGE_FOR_WHAT_GO_BACK_LEAVE                                           = 14416,  -- Exchange for what? %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. %. Go back. Leave.
        ARE_YOU_SURE_YOU_WANT_THE_YES_NO                                          = 14417,  -- Are you sure you want the %? Yes. No.
        ONCE_THE_EXCHANGE_IS_MADE_YOU_CANNOT_TAKE                                 = 14418,  -- Once the exchange is made, you cannot take it back. Are you absolutely sure you want to proceed?
        YOU_HAVE_ALREADY_EXCHANGED_FOR_THIS_ITEM                                  = 14419,  -- You have already exchanged for this item.
